Package: dumdum
Title: An Easy Way to Make Dummy (Binary) Variables
Version: 0.8.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Peter",
           family = "Licari",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "prlicari13@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9701-6006"))
Description: dumdum allows for users to easily create dummy variables from factor, string, or numeric variables. Users can make dummy variables, specify which variables (if any) they want to preserve as a reference category, and automatically rename the constructed variables to their specifications.
Depends: R (>= 3.0.1)
License: use_mit_license()
